      <originalsloc id="aspace_0e0e38dec9d02843c8df537f4d5d4399">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection is available on microfilm (HM 229) and in the Silvain Van Praet Papers (MS 1241).   The papers are principally a manuscript diary kept in English in twelve school notebooks by Silvain van Praet, a member of the Ostend (Belgium) city government, from the day of the German occupation of Ostend (1914 October 14) until its liberation (1918 October 17). It was concealed in a hole in the wall of the Maison Communal. There is also a typescript copy of the manuscript (568 p.) and several related documents.</p>  
      </originalsloc>
